The report points out the current US approach to China will have knock-on effects. Firstly, US global partners will increasingly question the longevity and wisdom of this approach, and their confidence in the US will be shaken as a result; (3/5)

The report argues Washington and Beijing can still develop a more durable and constructive relationship that is in the interests of the US and China. If Washington does not adjust its policy towards China, the US-China relationship will not be the worst, but only worse.(2/5)

A report by three Brookings Institution scholars Ryan Hass, Patricia M. Kim & Jeffrey A. Bader, said US China policy must be adjusted because  the US/China relationship is too important. Deterioration and confrontation cannot be the only option and perspective. (1/5)
